# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Pink Petals — environment variables
#
# Copy this file to `.env` (or `.env.local`) and fill in your Supabase project
# credentials. Find them in the Supabase dashboard → Project Settings → API.
#
# Both are SAFE to ship in the client bundle: the anon key only grants the
# access allowed by your Row-Level-Security policies (see supabase/schema.sql).
#
# Leave these BLANK to run the app in fully local, no-account mode — the PWA
# works offline exactly as before and the sign-in screen is skipped.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Your Supabase project URL, e.g. https://abcdefghijklm.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=

# Your Supabase anon / public API key (a long JWT-looking string)
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Database setup (first time only)
#
# Run supabase/schema.sql in your Supabase Dashboard → SQL Editor to create
# the required tables (profiles, user_data, otp_codes) and functions
# (generate_otp, verify_otp). Or use the automated script:
#
#   SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN=your_token node scripts/apply-schema.mjs
#
# Generate a personal access token at:
#   https://supabase.com/dashboard/account/tokens
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Email delivery (optional — the code is always shown on screen)
#
# Uses SMTP (e.g. Brevo / SendinBlue) to deliver the OTP code by email.
# Set these as Supabase secrets, not in .env:
#
#   npx supabase secrets set SMTP_HOST=smtp-relay.brevo.com
#   npx supabase secrets set SMTP_PORT=587
#   npx supabase secrets set SMTP_USER=b07c65001@smtp-brevo.com
#   npx supabase secrets set SMTP_PASS=your_smtp_password
#   npx supabase secrets set SEND_OTP_FROM="Pink Petals <noreply@yourdomain.com>"
#
# Deploy the edge function:
#   npx supabase functions deploy send-otp --no-verify-jwt
#
# When the function isn't deployed, the code appears on screen so you can
# copy it manually. All values above are the Brevo defaults.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
